Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of operations to make the given number 0. We can use a bitwise AND operation to repeatedly remove the highest power of 2 from the number until it becomes 0. The time complexity is O(log(n)) because we perform the operation log(n) times, where n is the given number. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the result variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs bitwise operations, which are energy-efficient compared to other operations.

